values: 警告；提醒；告诫；劝告；使警觉；发出警报；使警惕；提醒注意（可能发生的事）

sub_affix_info_list.affix_mean: suffix 表示“发展”、“创造”或“状态的加剧”:widen | deepen | loosen

word_mean_info__list.difference: 含义与caution相同，但语气较重，尤指重后果。
主要指针对有潜在危险而提出的警告，含小心从事的意味。
普通用词，泛指劝告，不涉及对方是否听从劝告。
一般指年长者或领导对已犯错误的或有过失的人提出的忠告或警告以避免类似错误。
正式用词，语气比advise强一些，侧重指对重要问题提出的劝告、建议或咨询。

word_group.brief_definition: 警告；告诫；告诫（某人）提防...
警告…离开；告诫…不得靠近；告诫…不要参与
警告作恶者；告诫做坏事的人；警告坏人

bilingual.source: It is difficult to warn people about them.
bilingual.target: 很难警告人们注意地震。

bilingual.source: He warn us not to go near the river.
bilingual.target: 他警告我们不要靠近那条河。

bilingual.source: The doctor warn him not to smoke again.
bilingual.target: 医生警告他不要再抽烟了。

bilingual.source: Doctors warn against the dangers of smoking.
He warn us that this road is very dangerous.
bilingual.target: 他警告我们这条路很危险。

bilingual.source: The weather forecast warn of a storm today.
bilingual.target: 天气预报警告今天会有暴风雨。

bilingual.source: Doctors warn that stimulants can be addictive.
bilingual.target: 医生警告说兴奋剂可能会上瘾。

bilingual.source: The lifeguard blew his whistle to warn the swimmers.
bilingual.target: 救生员吹响了哨子警告游泳者。

bilingual.source: Some frogs have bright colors to warn predators.
bilingual.target: 有些青蛙有鲜艳的颜色来警告捕食者。

bilingual.source: The bus driver used the horn to warn the cyclist.
bilingual.target: 公交车司机按了喇叭警告骑自行车的人。

yingyinNormal.en: I didn't kill her. I tried to warn her.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我没杀她，我是想警告她

yingyinNormal.en: No, I think she is trying to warn us.
yingyinNormal.zh: 不，我觉得他好像在警告我们。

yingyinNormal.en: We have to warn them. Billions of people will perish.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我们得警告他们，数十亿人将死去。

yingyinNormal.en: I have to warn her. Warn who? Dolores. The things they do to her. The things you do to her. I have to protect her.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我必须警告她。警告谁？德洛丽丝，他们对她做的事，他们对她做的事，我必须保护她。

yingyinNormal.en: Look, I warn you right now, don't come down on me.
yingyinNormal.zh: 听着，我警告你，别跟我找茬。

yingyinNormal.en: Well, I warn you, Dr Clarkson and I will fight to the last ditch.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我警告你，克拉克森医生跟我会抵抗到底。

yingyinNormal.en: I did warn the President. And then she shot herself in the head?
yingyinNormal.zh: 我确实警告了总统。然后她就开枪自杀了吗？

yingyinNormal.en: Yes? I know you tried to warn me. But I didn't listen. I'm sorry.
yingyinNormal.zh: 有事？您当初想警告我，但我没听您的，对不起。
yingyinNormal.videoNameZh: 《爱丽丝梦游仙境2：镜中奇遇记》

yingyinNormal.en: It's really scary. Don't say I didn't warn you. This better be good.
yingyinNormal.zh: 真的很吓人，可别说我没警告过你们。这故事最好真的精彩。

yingyinNormal.en: You went there to warn her. Still one problem with your story. Why did you bring the gun?
yingyinNormal.zh: 你去那儿警告她，但还是有一个问题，你为什么带着枪？

yingyinNormal.en: Your criminal records have also been expunged. However, I have to warn you against breaking any laws in the future.
yingyinNormal.zh: 你们的前科纪录也都撤销了，但我得警告你们未来别再犯法。

yingyinNormal.en: You knew this and you didn't warn them? Little girl, you can go to a pretty dark place when you on death row.
yingyinNormal.zh: 你为什么不警告他们？小女孩，天晓得我被折磨到想报仇的心有多可怕。

yingyinNormal.en: By all means warn him, I have spent enough elvish blood in defense of this accursed land, no more.
yingyinNormal.zh: 那你务必警告他，我已牺牲太多精灵来守卫这片被诅咒的土地了，我不会再继续。
yingyinNormal.videoNameEn: 《The Hobbit: The Battle of the Five Armies》

yingyinNormal.en: I'm sure there's no need to remind you, but if any of those who may be tempted to warn or turn themselves in to the authorities...
yingyinNormal.zh: 我相信应该不用警告你们,但只要有人自认聪明去向警察通报或自首…

yingyinNormal.en: You used the tunnels to infiltrate yourself into the White House, somehow conning your way into the blue sector, all to try and warn her?
yingyinNormal.zh: 你之前从隧道侵入白宫，还想办法进入到了蓝区，你做这些都是为了警告她吗

yingyinNormal.en: But I was very, very impressed by how intently you tried to warn me. I never thought I would say this, Andrea.
yingyinNormal.zh: 但是，当你想方设法的试图警告我时，我还是非常、非常的感动。我从没想过我会对你说这些，安吉丽雅…

yingyinNormal.en: No, it would just freak him out. Listen, before we leave, I should warn you, I'm a passionate man and I tend towards public displays of affection.
yingyinNormal.zh: 才不咧，那会吓坏他的，听着，在出发之前，我要警告你，我是个热情的男人，倾向于公开地表达我炙热的感情。

yingyinNormal.en: Miss Bennet, I warn you, I am not to be trifled with. A report of a most alarming nature has reached me, that you intend to be united with my nephew, Mr. Darcy.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我警告你，我是决不肯让人家来跟我开玩笑的。我听到一个极其惊人的消息，你快要攀上我的侄儿，达西先生。

yingyinNormal.en: Fine. I'll warn them myself.
yingyinNormal.zh: 那好，我自己去提醒他们。
yingyinNormal.videoNameZh: 《爱丽丝梦游仙境2：镜中奇遇记》

yingyinNormal.en: I programmed it in to warn me of an imminent system shutdown.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我编程让它在系统面临紧急关闭威胁时警示我。

examination_example.sentence: What does the author <highlight>warn</highlight> against in the passage?
examination_example.sentence_trans: 作者在文章中警告了什么？

examination_example.sentence: At 43, I've reached the stage where women are <highlight>warned</highlight> to watch out for the creeping sadness of middle age.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 43岁时，我已经到了这样一个阶段:女性被警告要警惕中年时期逐渐蔓延的悲伤情绪。

examination_example.sentence: Nigeria's minister of agriculture, has <highlight>warned</highlight> that the pest may "create serious problems for food security" in the country.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 尼日利亚(Nigeria)农业部长发出警告称，这种害虫可能会“给该国的粮食安全造成严重问题”。

sense_info_list.zh: 提醒; 告诫; 劝告(有所防备)

examination_example.sentence: The researchers, however, exercise caution by <highlight>warning</highlight> no one single response is the perfect remedy.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 然而，研究人员谨慎地警告说，没有一种单一的反应是完美的补救办法。

word_usage.usage:
warn sb. to do sth.表示“提醒某人做某事”，这里只能用不定式，不能用其他形式。
示例：我提醒他马上离开。
误 I warned him leaving at once.
正 I warned him to leave at once.

表示“提醒某人某事”可以用warn sb. of/about sth.。
示例：He warns me of the danger.
他提醒我注意那危险.

examination_example.sentence: A poisonous fish which has a sting strong enough to kill a human is invading the Mediterranean, <highlight>warn</highlight> scientists.

examination_example.sentence: What's more, making obesity a disease "may not benefit patients," he <highlight>warns</highlight>.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 此外，他警告说，把肥胖变成一种疾病“可能对病人没有好处”。
